                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.52/2065a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-12T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 12, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>217. Your 211 December 11, 1 p.m.<note n="23" xml:id="d586fn23">Not
                        printed.</note> In your forthcoming conference with the President of Mexico
                    the Department authorizes you in your discretion to discuss the Yaqui Valley
                    situation, being guided by your knowledge of the status of the proposals
                    submitted by the landowners.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
